NE}}\n* 2nd from Continent 1 (3rd place Europe 2010):<br /> {{hbw|ROM}}\n* 2nd from Continent 4 (2nd place Asia 2011):<br /> {{hbw|JPN}}\n|\n* 3rd from World (3rd place World 2011):<br /> {{hbw|ESP}}\n* 6th from World (7th place World 2011):<br /> {{hbw|CRO}}\n* 2nd from Continent 2 (2nd place Americas 2011):<br /> {{hbw|ARG}}\n* 3rd from Continent 1 (8th place Europe 2010):<br /> {{hbw|NED}}\n|\n* 4th from World (4th place World 2011):<br /> {{hbw|DEN}}\n* 5th from World (6th place World 2011):<br /> {{hbw|RUS}}\n* 2nd from Continent 3 (2nd place Africa 2012):<br /> {{hbw|TUN}}\n* 3rd from Continent 2 (3rd place Americas 2011):<br /> {{hbw|DOM}}\n|}\n\nNote :\n\n* Continents are ranked based on the 2011 World Championship results.\n* If the Oceania representative at the 2011 World Championship had placed from 8th to 12th, Oceania would have earned a spot for IHF Qualification Tournament #3 : Oceania\u2019s representative (Australia) placed 24th so, Dominican Republic, 3rd from Continent 2 (3rd place Americas 2011), are qualified.\n\n=== 2012 IHF Qualification Tournament #1 ===\n\n*Venue: {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Palais des Sports de Gerland]], [[Lyon]], [[France]]\n*All times are [[Central European Time]] ([[UTC+01:00]]).\n\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|show_positions=n\n|sortable_table=y\n|winpoints=2\n\n|team1=MNE|name_MNE={{hbw|MNE}}\n|team2=FRA|name_FRA={{hbw|FRA}}\n|team3=ROU|name_ROU={{hbw|ROU}}\n|team4=JPN|name_JPN={{hbw|JPN}}\n|win_MNE=3|draw_MNE=0|loss_MNE=0|gf_MNE=86|ga_MNE=67\n|win_FRA=2|draw_FRA=0|loss_FRA=1|gf_FRA=74|ga_FRA=58\n|win_ROU=1|draw_ROU=0|loss_ROU=2|gf_ROU=70|ga_ROU=84\n|win_JPN=0|draw_JPN=0|loss_JPN=3|gf_JPN=67|ga_JPN=88\n\n|col_A=#ccccff|text_A=\n|result1=A|result2=A\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n\n{{handballbox\n|date= 25 May 2012\n|time= 16:45\n|team1= {{hbw-rt|MNE}}\n|score= 30 \u2212 24\n|team2= {{hbw|JPN}}\n|report= [http://ihf.info/files/CompetitionData/132/pdf/01OMR.PDF Report]\n|goals1= [[Katarina Bulatovi\