ympic Qualification Women]]\n[[Category:Handball at the 2012 Summer Olympics|Q]]\n[[Category:Qualification for handball competitions|Olympics]]\n[[Category:2012 in women's handball|Olymp]]\n[[Category:Women's events at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n", "text_old": "{{other uses|Handball at the 2012 Summer Olympics (disambiguation)}}\nThe '''qualification for the [[Handball at the 2012 Summer Olympics|2012 Women's Olympic Handball Tournament]]''' is held from December 2010 to May 2012.\n{{TOCLimit|3}}\n\n==Qualification summary==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=75%\n|-\n! !! Date !! Venue !! Vacancies !! Qualified\n|-\n| Host Nation || || || align=\"center\"| 1 || {{hbw|GBR}}\n|-\n| [[2010 European Women's Handball Championship|2010 European Championship]] || 7\u201319 December 2010 || {{DEN}} & {{NOR}} || align=\"center\"| 1 || {{hbw|SWE}} <sup> [[#Notes1|*]] </sup>\n|-\n| 2011 Asian Olympic Qualification Tournament 2011 || 12\u201321 October || {{CHN}} || align=\"center\"| 1 || {{hbw|KOR}}\n|-\n| [[Handball at the 2011 Pan American Games \u2013 Women's tournament|2011 Pan American Games]] || 15\u201323 October 2011 || {{MEX}} || align=\"center\"| 1 || {{hbw|BRA}}\n|-\n| [[2011 World Women's Handball Championship|2011 World Championship]] || 2\u201318 December 2011 || {{BRA}} || align=\"center\"| 1 || {{hbw|NOR}}\n|-\n| [[2012 African Women's Handball Championship|2012 African Championship]] || 11\u201320 January 2012 || {{MAR}} || align=\"center\"| 1 || {{hbw|ANG}}\n|-\n| 2012 IHF Qualification Tournament #1 || 25\u201327 May 2012 || {{FRA}} || align=\"center\"| 2 || {{hbw|MNE}} <br /> {{hbw|FRA}}\n|-\n| 2012 IHF Qualification Tournament #2 || 25\u201327 May 2012 || {{ESP}} || align=\"center\"| 2 || {{hbw|ESP}} <br /> {{hbw|CRO}}\n|-\n| 2012 IHF Qualification Tournament #3 || 25\u201327 May 2012 || {{DEN}} || align=\"center\"| 2 || {{hbw|RUS}} <br /> {{hbw|DEN}}\n|-\n! Total !! colspan=\"2\"| !! 12 !!\n|}\n\n<div id=\"Notes1\"></div>\n:<sup> * </sup> Sweden qualified as