izes, Lasker (clinical medicine) awards and Gairdner awards (NLG metric)\n  | author     = Bruce G. Charlton\n  | journal    = Medical Hypotheses\n  | volume     = 69\n  | issue      = 1\n  | pages      = 1\u20135\n  | doi        = 10.1016/j.mehy.2007.01.001\n  | date       = 2007\n | pmid = 17276606\n |access-date=27 March 2020\n  }}</ref>\n<ref name=biomedicine2>{{cite web\n  | url        = https://www.the-scientist.com/the-nutshell/prizes-bigger-than-the-nobel-30786\n  | title      = Prizes Bigger than the Nobel\n  | author     = Shawna Williams\n  | work       = The Scientist\n  | date       = 5 October 2017\n  }}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{Nobel Prizes}}\n{{Phaleristics}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Prizes known as the Nobel of a field}}\n[[Category:Lists of awards|Nobel of a field]]\n", "name_user": "Poppopsun", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_prizes_known_as_the_Nobel_of_a_field"}
{"title_page": "Annabel Dimmock", "text_new": "{{Infobox golfer\n| name              = Annabel Dimmock\n| image             = \n| image_size        = \n| caption           = \n| fullname          =\n| nickname          =\n| birth_date        = {{Birth date and age|1996|10|5|df=y}}\n| birth_place       = [[London]], England\n| death_date        = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|1996|10|5|df=y}} -->\n| death_place       =\n| height            = {{height|ft=5|in=6}}\n| weight            =\n| nationality       = {{ENG}}\n| residence         = [[London]], England\n| spouse            =\n| partner           =\n| children          =\n| college           =\n| yearpro           = 2016\n| retired           = <!-- Year retired -->\n| tour              = [[Ladies European Tour]]\n| extour            = <!-- Former tours which a member of -->\n| prowins           = 1\n| lpgawins          = \n| letwins           = 1\n| jlpgawins         = <!-- LPGA of Japan Tour wins -->\n| klpgawins         = <!-- LPGA of Korea Tour wins -->\n| lagtwins          = <!-- Number of Ladies Asian Golf Tour wins -->\n| alpgwins          = <!-- Number of ALPG Tour wins -->\n| futwins           = <!-- Number of Futures Tour wins -->\n| otherwins         = <!-- Number of Other wins -->\n| majorwins         = <!-- Number of Major Championship wins -->\n| nabisco           = DNP\n| lpga              = DNP\n| wusopen           = DNP\n| wbritopen         = 69: 2019\n| evian             = MC: 2019\n| wghofid           = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame member ID -->\n| wghofyear         = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame year inducted -->\n| award1            = \n| year1             = \n| awardssection     = <!-- location of awards page or section -->\n}}\n'''Annabel Dimmock''' (born 5 October 1996) is an English [[professional golfer]].\n\n==Amateur career==\nAs an amateur Dimmock won the Helen Holm Scottish Open and the Jones/Doherty Cup.<ref name=\"TeamGB\"/> She was a member of the England Golf National Girl's squad and represented Europe in the 2014 [[Junior Ryder Cup]], Great Britain and Ireland in the [[2014 Curtis Cup]] and [[Great Britain at the 2014 Summer Youth Olympics]].<ref name=\"TeamGB\">{{cite web |title=Biography Annabel Dimmock |url=https://www.teamgb.com/athletes/annabel-dimmock |publisher=Team GB |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\nDimmock turned professional in 2016 and finished third at the 2017 [[Lalla Meryem Cup]] before holding off French amateur Pauline Roussin Bouchard to win her first [[Ladies European Tour]] and [[LET Access Series]] title by one shot in the 2019 [[Jabra Ladies Open]], as she also qualified for the [[2019 Evian Championship]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Annabel Dimmock wins Jabra Ladies Open |url=https://ladieseuropeantour.com/jabra-ladies-open-annabel-dimmock-wins-first-let-title/ |publisher=Ladies European Tour |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Professional wins (1)==\n===Ladies European Tour (1)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!No.\n!Date\n!Tournament\n!Winning<br>score\n!To par\n!Margin<br>of victory\n!Runner-up\n!Winner's<br>share ([[Euro|\u20ac]])\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|align=right|25 May [[2019 Ladies European Tour|2019]]\n|[[Jabra Ladies Open]]\n|align=right|69-69-68=206\n|align=center|\u22127\n|1 stroke\n|{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Pauline Roussin Bouchard]] (am)\n|align=center|24,400\n|}\n\n==Team appearances==\n'''Amateur'''\n*[[Junior Ryder Cup]] (representing Europe): 2014\n*[[Curtis Cup]] (representing Great Britain and Ireland): [[2014 Curtis Cup|2014]]\n\n'''Professional'''\n*[[The Queens (golf)|The Queens]] (representing Europe): 2017\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{LadiesEuroTour player|200741}}\n*{{WWGR|5881}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dimmock, Annabel}}\n[[Category:English female golfers]]\n[[Category:Ladies European Tour golfers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from London]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox golfer\n| name              = Annabel Dimmock\n| image             = \n| image_size        = \n| caption           = \n| fullname          =\n| nickname          =\n| birth_date        = {{Birth date and age|1996|10|5|df=y}}\n| birth_place       = [[London]], England\n| death_date        = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|1996|10|5|df=y}} -->\n| death_place       =\n| height            = {{height|ft=5|in=6}}\n| weight            =\n| nationality       = {{ENG}}\n| residence         = [[London]], England\n| spouse            =\n| partner           =\n| children          =\n| college           =\n| yearpro           = 2016\n| retired           = <!-- Year retired -->\n| tour              = [[Ladies European Tour]]\n| extour            = <!-- Former tours which a member of -->\n| prowins           = 1\n| lpgawins          = \n| letwins           = 1\n| jlpgawins         = <!-- LPGA of Japan Tour wins -->\n| klpgawins         = <!-- LPGA of Korea Tour wins -->\n| lagtwins          = <!-- Number of Ladies Asian Golf Tour wins -->\n| alpgwins          = <!-- Number of ALPG Tour wins -->\n| futwins           = <!-- Number of Futures Tour wins -->\n| otherwins         = <!-- Number of Other wins -->\n| majorwins         = <!-- Number of Major Championship wins -->\n| nabisco           = DNP\n| lpga              = DNP\n| wusopen           = DNP\n| wbritopen         = 69: 2019\n| evian             = MC: 2019\n| wghofid           = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame member ID -->\n| wghofyear         = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame year inducted -->\n| award1            = \n| year1             = \n| awardssection     = <!-- location of awards page or section -->\n}}\n'''Annabel Dimmock''' (born 5 October 1996) is an English [[professional golfer]].\n\n==Amateur career==\nAs an amateur Dimmock won the Helen Holm Scottish Open and the Jones/Doherty Cup.<ref name=\"TeamGB\"/> She was a member of the England Golf National Girl\u2019s squad and represented Europe in the 2014 [[Junior Ryder Cup]], Great Britain and Ireland in the [[2014 Curtis Cup]] and [[Great Britain at the 2014 Summer Youth Olympics]].<ref name=\"TeamGB\">{{cite web |title=Biography Annabel Dimmock |url=https://www.teamgb.com/athletes/annabel-dimmock |publisher=Team GB |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\nDimmock turned professional in 2016 and finished third at the 2017 [[Lalla Meryem Cup]] before holding off French amateur Pauline Roussin Bouchard to win her first [[Ladies European Tour]] and [[LET Access Series]] title by one shot in the 2019 [[Jabra Ladies Open]], as she also qualified for the [[2019 Evian Championship]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Annabel Dimmock wins Jabra Ladies Open |url=https://ladieseuropeantour.com/jabra-ladies-open-annabel-dimmock-wins-first-let-title/ |publisher=Ladies European Tour |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Professional wins (1)==\n===Ladies European Tour (1)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!No.\n!Date\n!Tournament\n!Winning<br>score\n!To par\n!Margin<br>of victory\n!Runner-up\n!Winner's<br>share ([[Euro|\u20ac]])\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|align=right|25 May [[2019 Ladies European Tour|2019]]\n|[[Jabra Ladies Open]]\n|align=right|69-69-68=206\n|align=center|\u22127\n|1 stroke\n|{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Pauline Roussin Bouchard]] (am)\n|align=center|24,400\n|}\n\n==Team appearances==\n'''Amateur'''\n*[[Junior Ryder Cup]] (representing Europe): 2014\n*[[Curtis Cup]] (representing Great Britain and Ireland): [[2014 Curtis Cup|2014]]\n\n'''Professional'''\n*[[The Queens (golf)|The Queens]] (representing Europe): 2017\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{LadiesEuroTour player|200741}}\n*{{WWGR|5881}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dimmock, Annabel}}\n[[Category:English female golfers]]\n[[Category:Ladies European Tour golfers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from London]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAmateur career:cl